          <h2>Consent Requirements for Businesses</h2>
          <p>FilterFive requires all subscribing businesses to obtain <strong>prior express written consent</strong> before submitting any customer phone numbers. This section documents our consent requirements.</p>

          <h3 id="required-elements">Required Consent Elements</h3>
          <p>All consent collection must include:</p>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Business Identification</strong> — Clear identification of the business name</li>
            <li><strong>Message Description</strong> — Clear statement that the customer will receive an SMS review request</li>
            <li><strong>Frequency Disclosure</strong> — Statement that this is a one-time message</li>
            <li><strong>Rate Disclosure</strong> — "Message and data rates may apply"</li>
            <li><strong>Opt-Out Instructions</strong> — "Reply STOP to opt out"</li>
            <li><strong>Policy Links</strong> — References to terms of service and privacy policy</li>
          </ol>

          <h3 id="digital-consent">Approved Digital Consent Language</h3>
          <p>Businesses must use consent language substantially similar to:</p>

          <h4>Standard Checkbox Consent</h4>
          <p><strong>For web forms, booking systems, and digital intake forms:</strong></p>
          <pre><code>☐ I agree to receive a one-time SMS review request from [Business Name].
  Message and data rates may apply. Reply STOP to opt out.
  Terms: [link] | Privacy: [link]</code></pre>

          <h4>Expanded Consent Language</h4>
          <p><strong>For businesses preferring more detailed disclosure:</strong></p>
          <pre><code>☐ SMS Consent: By checking this box, I consent to receive a one-time
  text message from [Business Name] requesting feedback about my visit.
  Message frequency: 1 message. Message and data rates may apply.
  Reply STOP to cancel. View our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy.</code></pre>

